# Scaffold Connector

> **Status: stub — implementation pending.** Contract only. Consolidates
> the module-generation half of
> `narrative-connectors/.claude/skills/create-connector` (the sbt module
> set, build.sbt + QuickPublish wiring, ops docs) — infra, DB, and
> registration are split into their own skills in this plugin.

## Purpose

Produce the connector's Scala module skeleton so the implementation skills
have somewhere to write. Copies the reference connector's module set
(`<slug>-{api,services,stores,worker,executor,poller}`), rewrites package
and identifier names, and wires the new modules into `build.sbt` and
`QuickPublish.scala`, plus the `<slug>/` ops-docs directory.

Phase: **service** (the first code-generation step).

## Inputs (from connector-spec.yaml)

- `slug`, `package_slug` — module directory names, Scala package, image
  names.
- `destination_type` — which modules are relevant (e.g. poller only when
  measurement is in scope).
- Modules to omit (optional).

## Outputs

- `<slug>-{api,services,stores,worker,executor,poller}` modules.
- `build.sbt` `lazy val`s + aggregate-root entries; `QuickPublish.scala`
  flags.
- `<slug>/` ops docs (operations.md, README, architecture.md, CHANGES.md).

## Human gates

- Local codegen only — every file is a reviewable working-tree change.
- **Out of scope here:** no `terraform`, no narrative-db migrations, no
  app registration. Those are `/scaffold-connector-infra`,
  `/provision-connector-db`, and `/register-connector-app`.

